text: Hmm. Definitely a nicely edited trailer in any case, and it'll be good to see some mindless action with a bit of budgetary oomph behind it. That said, this film seems completely out of sorts compared to the first four. Rambo's always been about this history-less, stoic soldier who does not get attached to anyone except his CO, Trautman. From the very first film almost no reference has ever been made to Rambo's pre-Vietnam history. This has been a defining feature of the character - the idea that one could believe that he came out of the womb with that killer instinct, that you could never imagine him as a child, with family, happy. That's what made the final shot of the postbox in Rambo 4 so jarring - it was meant to represent Rambo ending his war and finally finding peace.

text: I rented first blood in 1983 at Arcade video in Ridgefield Connecticut. When we moved back to Norway in 1984 my dad gave me this so I could watch it while I missed the Place I lived 7 years as a kid growing up. In 1985 Rambo became this huge thing and the Movie was illegal in Norway back then. My dad bought a prate copy in saudi Arabia on a business trip so I loved that. In 1988 my friend and I saw it in the Movie theatre in Tønsberg Norway and had fun. In 2008 my dad bought number 4 on dvd in China for me and I loved it. Will see this NeXT one in the theatre With my mom for her 73 birthday.
